    <div id="container4">
        <div>
            <div style="width:90%;">
                <p1>
                    These brief screenings are the quickest way to determine if you or someone you care about should connect with a mental health professional. They are completely anonymous and confidential, and immediately following the brief questionnaire you will see your results, recommendations, and key resources. <br>
                    - Elevated: further evaluation is recommended. Scores for any of the scales that fall in the elevated range typically indicate that you may be experiencing high distress in that area. You would benefit from calling to schedule a Quick Care consultation at CAPS (801-422-3035 (tel:801-422-3035)).
                <br>- Moderate: Scores in the moderate range indicate some potential areas of concern. If these concerns are problematic you may consider further evaluation, or you may consider accessing our online self-help resources, found here (https://caps.byu.edu/evidence-based-online-help).
                <br>- Low: no action is needed at this time. This indicates that this is an area in which you may be functioning normally.</p1>
            </div>          
        </div>
        <div style="width:43%">
            <p1>Amidst the vast digital landscape, we recognize the importance of mental well-being. That's why we proudly introduce SafeUT, a crisis text and tip line service developed by the University of Utah. SafeUT provides a confidential and anonymous platform for individuals, especially students, to connect with trained crisis counselors 24/7.<br>

                How SafeUT Works:
                <br>-Crisis Text Line: Access immediate support by texting a crisis counselor directly.
                <br>-Anonymous Tips: Report concerns related to mental health, bullying, or other challenges, promoting a safer online community.
                <br>
                Why SafeUT Matters:
                <br>-Social media can have profound effects on mental health, and SafeUT serves as a lifeline for those navigating the complexities of the digital world. By raising awareness and providing a resource like SafeUT, we aim to contribute to a healthier, more supportive online environment.
                <br>
                Join us in promoting social media literacy and mental health awareness. Together, we can make a positive impact in the digital realm.
            </p1>
